The paper focuses on clinical text structuring using a novel model that introduces domain-specific features into pre-trained language models. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as it specifically deals with NLP. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new model for the task. cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories as they cover related topics such as text classification and neural networks.
